docs.abstract: The president’s lawyers are struggling to understand where the investigations surrounding him are going, and the extent of his legal exposure.
docs.snippet: The president’s lawyers are struggling to understand where the investigations surrounding him are going, and the extent of his legal exposure.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Nearly a dozen lawyers now assist President Trump in contending with two federal investigations, one in Washington and one in New York, that could pose serious threats to his presidency and his businesses. But the expanding legal team is struggling to understand where the investigations could be headed and the extent of Mr. Trump’s legal exposure.

headline.main: Trump’s Growing Legal Team Has a Problem: It’s Operating Partly in the Dark
headline.print_headline: Lawyers Work At Untangling Risk to Trump

docs.abstract: The president again chooses confrontation over conciliation. His caustic approach to politics echoes through the rest of the political food chain.
docs.snippet: The president again chooses confrontation over conciliation. His caustic approach to politics echoes through the rest of the political food chain.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In moments of national crisis, presidents typically reach for unifying themes, as Bill Clinton did after the Oklahoma City bombing and George W. Bush did with the bullhorn on the wrecked fire truck after 9/11. President Trump on Thursday chose confrontation over conciliation.

headline.main: Trump, Partisan and Pugilist, Abandons Calls for Unity After Bomb Scares
